The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, March 17, 2004 				 Writers tryst
 A STAFF REPORTER																								UK-based writer Christopher Eagar, who missed an appointment with transport minister Subhas Chakraborty on Friday, as he was kept waiting for over two hours by staff of the information and cultural affairs department at Writers Buildings, finally got to meet him on Tuesday.																								After the report was published in Metro, the minister himself called up Eagar on Monday and called him over to Netaji Indoor Stadium. This time, the ministers men were waiting at the entrance to escort Eagar to Chakrabortys chamber. The writer was gifted a T-shirt and a hat with a picture of Netaji.
